1
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:28,120
In the first round of tests,

2
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,720
all you Special Agents shone.

3
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,960
But this is only the cruel prologue.

4
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:35,720
The final number of Agent Badges

5
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,360
and the skydiving challenge

6
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:40,280
will be decided by this lakeside.

7
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:47,560
After testing everyone’s

8
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,600
disguise skills,

9
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:49,320
the second round

10
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:49,840
will now test

11
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,800
your one‑on‑one

12
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,000
head‑to‑head combat

13
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,120
attack and defense skills.

14
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,680
This mission is called

15
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,040
The Person in the Wind.

16
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:06,920
It’s also An Yu’s brand‑new single

17
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,680
just released today

18
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,560
at twelve, written by himself.

19
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,920
Sorry, thanks.

20
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,400
So he even writes lyrics.

21
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,240
The eight members will battle

22
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,840
each other one on one.

23
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,920
Each pair of players

24
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,080
holds a candle

25
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,200
and a fan.

26
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,600
They must follow the music

27
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,320
and dance,

28
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,040
while making sure

29
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:27,280
their own candle stays lit,

30
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:29,760
and fan out the other’s.

31
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:30,920
The winner advances

32
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,400
to the next round.

33
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,520
The final champion will win

34
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,520
an Agent Badge.

35
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,480
For our first battle,

36
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,720
these two “Great Generals” go up.

37
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,440
Bring the candles.

38
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,640
It’s out.

39
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:58,080
Won.

40
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,840
Come on down.

41
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,240
Bring the fans.

42
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,960
These two really are evenly matched.

43
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,960
Forget the game, they’re posing first.

44
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,040
Convinced now?

45
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:56,920
“General.”

46
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,880
Chengcheng, come on.

47
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,320
You’re giving him cupping marks.

48
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:09,960
Come on.

49
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,360
Let’s go.

50
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,560
Bing Ge.

51
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:27,760
Teach him a lesson.

52
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,920
Let him see clearly

53
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,040
how Northeasterners play this.

54
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,480
Come on.

55
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:33,800
Come on.

56
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,520
Start fanning.

57
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,680
Magic trick.

58
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,120
That was crisp.

59
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,320
Come on, Jingyu.

60
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,720
Come on, big Jingyu.

61
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,440
Sir Huang.

62
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,520
Sir Huang, only you can stop him.

63
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,720
The guests are going to crush us.

64
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,360
No hitting people.

65
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,320
We really can’t beat them.

66
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,600
I’ll blow you out now.

67
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,080
Come on.

68
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:24,760
Okay.

69
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:33,360
It looks like

70
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,440
nothing’s happening,

71
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,080
but they’re secretly straining.

72
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,560
Defend.

73
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,160
This is

74
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:02,760
a dance.

75
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:11,840
Looks pretty good.

76
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,440
Yeah, fan him as a person too.

77
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,280
Fan him till he catches a cold.

78
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:26,400
Can this really decide a winner?

79
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:38,880
They’re stirring, here they go.

80
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:41,960
Blow with your mouth.

81
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,320
Wrap it up soon.

82
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,400
They’ll fall in love at this rate.

83
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,320
Attack.

84
00:06:58,840 --> 00:06:59,920
Out.

85
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,360
Finally burned it down.

86
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,000
So it was slow‑burned out.

87
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,000
Finally boiled off his wax.

88
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,600
Xiao Hu.

89
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:17,960
Okay.

90
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,800
The style has changed.

91
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,120
See who gets a fever first.

92
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:37,960
Out.

93
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:38,520
Won.

94
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,760
You beat Brother Jingyu.

95
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,440
What, it’s finally me and Jin Chen?

96
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:47,720
Pick Teng Ge.

97
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,120
Pick me.

98
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,440
Let me deal with Daxi.

99
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,440
Fan him till he catches a cold.

100
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:25,760
Bro, you know…

101
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,320
Is this the candle‑blowing game?

102
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,320
I’m gonna fan you into a fever.

103
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,680
Still can’t blow this out?

104
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,920
Come on, Xiao Hu!

105
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,160
Teng Ge is out of breath now.

106
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,120
Honestly, even this doesn’t work?

107
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,040
It still hasn’t gone out.

108
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,480
You were about to sneak‑attack me?

109
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:12,800
No.

110
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,560
It’s not that kind.

111
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,400
Like those fake supermarket candles.

112
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,920
The rechargeable ones.

113
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,560
I fanned it like crazy twice,

114
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:23,120
and it still didn’t go out.

115
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,520
You try fanning it yourself.

116
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,880
Yours really won’t go out.

117
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,720
You see how hard it is for a veteran artist.

118
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,040
“Teasing the old man,” right?

119
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:46,720
“Teasing the old man.”

120
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,080
You blow out his, then.

121
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:54,560
Okay.

122
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,800
I’ve no faith at all.

123
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,560
No faith at all.

124
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,160
Awesome.

125
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:23,600
Been waiting for you forever.

126
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,360
Two fans and my legs feel ancient.

127
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,640
We blew it out together.

128
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:55,000
It’s a tie.

129
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:56,080
A tie.

130
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,400
Congrats.

131
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,160
In this round we’ll hand out

132
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,760
three Agent Badges.

133
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:04,880
Teng Ge and Daxi from the tie,

134
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,360
and the one with the most wins,

135
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:06,840
William.

136
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:11,520
Now we’re heading

137
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,440
back into the house

138
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:15,000
for our final round of tests.

139
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,040
What are you doing there?

140
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,640
I’m using Taobao Pailitao.

141
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,200
Look, same style found in seconds.

142
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,360
You can even buy Italian stuff here.

143
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:24,800
Of course.

144
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,440
With Pailitao you can also find

145
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,320
our Let’s Go Now family outfits.

146
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:28,880
For real?

147
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:29,640
Let me try.

148
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,080
Don’t tell me your top has a match too.

149
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:32,920
It really does.

150
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,120
Search “Let’s Go Now” on Taobao now

151
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,960
for a chance to get an 888 bonus.

152
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,600
I’ll try it too.

153
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:39,200
So much food!

154
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,040
Reflex reaction.

155
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:02,160
These guys are hilarious.

156
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,040
Xiao Hu didn’t react.

157
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,200
So he’s got no reflex.

158
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,520
He has no reflex.

159
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:10,640
What are you talking about?

160
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,160
Normally if you poke a guy like this

161
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:14,920
he tenses up hard right away.

162
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:15,920
Shows off his muscles.

163
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,200
Pretty much men everywhere

164
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:17,920
are like that.

165
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,440
Every inch.

166
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,640
Welcome to

167
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,520
my home in Italy.

168
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,840
Let’s not skip any dish.

169
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,560
Try a bit of everything.

170
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,920
Everything’s good, really.

171
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:50,880
Xiao Hu.

172
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,560
All this way,

173
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,840
have I treated you badly?

174
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:54,760
Not at all.

175
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,400
Bring me the pasta.

176
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,080
One fork and I’ll finish it.

177
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,360
Never thought

178
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:09,920
never in my life thought

179
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:10,960
pasta could taste this good.

180
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:17,960
Back then,

181
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,440
I invited this

182
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,160
Repin Academy of Fine Arts

183
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:23,560
Lifetime Honorary Professor

184
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,840
to paint this here.

185
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:27,560
They hung the middle one upside down.

186
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,320
Felt just like being home.

187
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,400
Next,

188
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,000
we’ll do our final round of tests.

189
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,760
We’ll test each Special Agent’s

190
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:36,600
judgment and language skills.

191
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,240
Soon we’ll battle in teams.

192
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:48,000
We’re already splitting teams, right?

193
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,680
Yeah.

194
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:49,760
My left side looks better.

195
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,520
I’ll stand on this side then.

196
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,360
Let me show you a stunning photo

197
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,360
I took of Teng Ge yesterday.

198
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,080
You’re annoying.

199
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,360
After two o’clock.

200
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,960
I was still pretty used to it.

201
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,000
Woke us right up.

202
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,880
It’s already past two.

203
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,800
This test is called

204
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,720
All members are split in two teams.

205
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,440
The two teams will take turns

206
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,960
Only The Knower knows the answer.

207
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,320
You must ask the Observation Team in English.

208
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,400
The Observation Team can only say yes or no.

209
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,160
When you guess the answer,

210
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,880
the team with fewer questions gets 1 point.

211
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,520
If they find The Knower, they get 1 point.

212
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,160
Do you know how this game works?

213
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,000
You haven’t told me yet.

214
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:48,760
Translate it for me.

215
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,600
Simply, it’s the four of us.

216
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,760
If you’re the one with the word,

217
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:58,400
you must guide the other three of us

218
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,440
to ask your team faster.

219
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,280
Then we have to guess the word

220
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:02,920
that’s written on your card.

221
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:05,280
Whichever team uses fewer guesses

222
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,160
is the team that wins.

223
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:06,920
But the one with the word

224
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:08,040
must really protect themselves

225
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,080
and not let the others find them.

226
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:09,920
Okay.

227
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,400
If you’re sure, say “yes.”

228
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,680
If you’re not sure, say “no.”

229
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:14,760
If it’s in‑between, could be or not,

230
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,240
if you’re unsure, say “both okay.”

231
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:17,760
When unsure I can’t say “no”?

232
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,320
Oh.

233
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,400
Oh.

234
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:21,880
In the Northeast we say “ngh.”

235
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:23,240
That works.

236
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,600
Okay, it’s clear now.

237
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:24,880
Come on.

238
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:25,960
Let’s guess first.

239
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,040
Everyone, close your eyes.

240
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:31,760
The Knower, hold up one finger.

241
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:33,800
Everyone, open your eyes.

242
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,200
Ask quickly.

243
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:36,680
Come on, ask.

244
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,520
Should we ask if it’s for use

245
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,040
and then if it’s food,

246
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:39,760
and then if it’s a person?

247
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,480
Or ask if it’s a drink?

248
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,320
Is it food, not a drink?

249
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,520
Food, not drink.

250
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,160
No, just ask if it goes in your mouth.

251
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:47,800
Isn’t that better?

252
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,760
Some people even eat crap though.

253
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,160
Should we ask

254
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:58,320
if it has three characters?

255
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:00,240
In Chinese.

256
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,840
Three Chinese characters.

257
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:02,880
Or three English letters?

258
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:03,320
Chinese, of course.

259
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,040
Then it must be Chinese.

260
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:06,520
Let me ask then.

261
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:06,880
You ask.

262
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:11,120
Is it three Chinese characters?

263
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:12,400
Yes.

264
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,200
Daxi.

265
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,560
The spy got exposed so fast.

266
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:20,760
No.

267
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:21,600
Remember,

268
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,840
Teng Ge said “three characters.”

269
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,880
I still think we should ask first

270
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,320
whether it’s something you use.

271
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,720
Chengcheng wants to ask “Is it used?”

272
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,560
That’s too far‑fetched.

273
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:31,960
I think

274
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:32,520
that’s too far.

275
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,160
I think ask if it’s used first.

276
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:42,600
You ask then.

277
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:06,920
Next one.

278
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:08,839
Start.

279
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:09,319
The one with the word

280
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:10,119
really has to protect themselves

281
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:11,359
and not be found by the others.

282
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,480
Something to eat.

283
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,720
Just one.

284
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,359
My name is Fan Chengcheng.

285
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:24,520
What’s your name?

286
00:17:28,119 --> 00:17:28,760
Both are okay.

287
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,720
After all those questions,

288
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,600
he asked Brother Jingyu,

289
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:35,920
“What’s your name called?”

290
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:37,640
Why?

291
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,440
