1161
00:52:12,280 --> 00:52:14,120
We’re up here already, too late now.

1162
00:52:19,200 --> 00:52:20,680
Sir Huang, why so quiet?

1163
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:23,320
I’m scared too.

1164
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:26,360
You two are such scared kids.

1165
00:52:28,800 --> 00:52:29,280
Bing Ge is still the brave one.

1166
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:30,760
So many protect you, why so tense?

1167
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:43,400
Only past the clouds is the sunset.

1168
00:52:53,480 --> 00:52:54,040
So beautiful.

1169
00:52:56,120 --> 00:52:56,560
Bro.

1170
00:52:57,400 --> 00:52:57,920
The sunset.

1171
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:01,560
It’s gorgeous.

1172
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:08,320
So beautiful.

1173
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:10,880
It’s gorgeous.

1174
00:53:11,600 --> 00:53:12,480
It’s gorgeous.

1175
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:13,200
This is amazing.

1176
00:53:15,240 --> 00:53:16,320
How high now, sis?

1177
00:53:17,320 --> 00:53:18,480
Three thousand three.

1178
00:53:18,960 --> 00:53:20,240
Nine hundred meters to go.

1179
00:53:23,800 --> 00:53:25,000
So I’m jumping first.

1180
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:26,240
Let Bing Ge go first.

1181
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:27,120
I’ll go first.

1182
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,600
Bing Ge asked to jump first.

1183
00:53:29,000 --> 00:53:29,680
He’ll be second.

1184
00:53:30,280 --> 00:53:31,560
That’s confirmed now, right?

1185
00:53:32,360 --> 00:53:33,600
Then I’ll be the first to go.

1186
00:53:34,520 --> 00:53:35,000
Bing Ge.

1187
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:40,080
Actually,

1188
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:41,800
I wanted to share this for you.

1189
00:53:41,800 --> 00:53:42,280
It’s fine.

1190
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:45,560
We two bros will guard him in center.

1191
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:54,600
Bing Ge.

1192
00:53:55,920 --> 00:53:56,480
Sir Huang.

1193
00:53:58,120 --> 00:53:59,200
Three, two, one.

1194
00:54:11,280 --> 00:54:12,640
I suddenly got nervous.

1195
00:54:38,960 --> 00:54:39,680
What height now?

1196
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:41,720
Four thousand two hundred.

1197
00:54:49,080 --> 00:54:50,320
At what height do we pull?

1198
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:51,160
One thousand eight hundred.

1199
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:54,880
What is it, an alarm?

1200
00:55:21,880 --> 00:55:22,680
Okay.

1201
00:55:32,520 --> 00:55:33,040
Let’s go!

1202
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:34,840
Bing Ge.

1203
00:55:35,840 --> 00:55:36,520
Sir Huang.

1204
00:55:37,320 --> 00:55:38,240
Come on, is it that bad?

1205
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:39,440
I’m scared.

1206
00:55:43,080 --> 00:55:44,520
My heart rate’s at one twenty.

1207
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:46,920
Only one twenty for you?

1208
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:48,760
My heart rate is—

1209
00:55:50,320 --> 00:55:51,160
Is that okay?

1210
00:55:51,160 --> 00:55:52,720
You got this.

1211
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:55,960
Who’ll be first?

1212
00:55:55,960 --> 00:55:57,240
I guess the first

1213
00:55:57,240 --> 00:55:57,760
will be Bing Ge.

1214
00:55:58,840 --> 00:56:00,120
Should be An Yu.

1215
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:04,920
Come on.

1216
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:24,760
It’s so cold.

1217
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:58,800
Everyone,

1218
00:57:00,240 --> 00:57:01,240
let’s go!

1219
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:21,240
You only live once.

1220
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:22,240
Everyone,

1221
00:57:22,480 --> 00:57:23,320
go!

1222
00:57:46,080 --> 00:57:47,640
We’re alive,

1223
00:58:04,320 --> 00:58:06,560
you only live once, friends!

1224
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:17,760
Let’s go!

1225
00:58:30,120 --> 00:58:30,880
So awesome!

1226
01:00:21,040 --> 01:00:21,800
They opened!

1227
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:33,080
Up there!

1228
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:33,720
I see them!

1229
01:00:33,720 --> 01:00:34,200
Where?

1230
01:00:37,920 --> 01:00:39,160
They opened.

1231
01:00:43,560 --> 01:00:44,320
All three chutes are open.

1232
01:00:46,800 --> 01:00:47,400
Yeah, they’re open.

1233
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:58,640
That one did a flip, see it?

1234
01:00:58,640 --> 01:00:59,480
That one.

1235
01:00:59,480 --> 01:01:00,680
What was that about, over there?

1236
01:01:00,680 --> 01:01:01,360
What’s going on here?

1237
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:01,720
Look at that.

1238
01:01:01,720 --> 01:01:02,360
It did a backflip in the air.

1239
01:01:02,360 --> 01:01:02,920
See that?

1240
01:01:02,920 --> 01:01:04,240
No, that one kept flipping.

1241
01:01:04,240 --> 01:01:05,000
That one.

1242
01:01:05,000 --> 01:01:05,800
That one too.

1243
01:01:05,800 --> 01:01:07,000
No.

1244
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:19,840
Thank you, coach.

1245
01:01:31,960 --> 01:01:33,040
Perfect.

1246
01:01:33,800 --> 01:01:35,080
This is a beautiful sky.

1247
01:01:35,080 --> 01:01:35,760
Yeah.

1248
01:01:41,880 --> 01:01:43,000
Are those your friends?

1249
01:01:45,320 --> 01:01:46,280
My friends.

1250
01:01:48,560 --> 01:01:49,840
And these?

1251
01:01:57,000 --> 01:01:58,480
Let’s go.

1252
01:01:59,360 --> 01:02:00,240
How did he end up there?

1253
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:01,480
Come back.

1254
01:02:02,160 --> 01:02:03,320
That one’s heading for the treetops.

1255
01:02:07,160 --> 01:02:08,000
That’s not An Yu, right?

1256
01:02:12,400 --> 01:02:14,680
When you skydive down from up there,

1257
01:02:14,680 --> 01:02:16,320
there are people below catching you.

1258
01:02:16,320 --> 01:02:17,360
It feels insanely good.

1259
01:02:17,360 --> 01:02:18,840
Here he comes.

1260
01:02:22,040 --> 01:02:22,720
Who’s this?

1261
01:02:23,160 --> 01:02:24,080
Who’s this?

1262
01:02:24,080 --> 01:02:24,840
Who’s this?

1263
01:02:28,320 --> 01:02:29,320
Bing Ge.

1264
01:02:34,920 --> 01:02:36,000
Bing Ge!

1265
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:37,120
That was amazing.

1266
01:02:37,880 --> 01:02:38,560
How was it?

1267
01:02:38,560 --> 01:02:39,080
It just…

1268
01:02:39,080 --> 01:02:40,360
It felt like I became immortal.

1269
01:02:42,920 --> 01:02:44,280
He’s here.

1270
01:02:49,400 --> 01:02:50,400
Who is that?

1271
01:02:50,960 --> 01:02:52,160
His face is so pale.

1272
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:54,120
Darn it, the jacket.

1273
01:02:54,120 --> 01:02:54,680
The jacket.

1274
01:02:55,000 --> 01:02:56,000
My jacket.

1275
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:56,720
The jacket.

1276
01:02:56,720 --> 01:02:57,560
Wang Anyu.

1277
01:03:06,640 --> 01:03:08,280
We’re still alive!

1278
01:03:09,040 --> 01:03:09,960
He’s crying.

1279
01:03:10,520 --> 01:03:11,560
He’s crying.

1280
01:03:12,640 --> 01:03:13,280
Scary or not?

1281
01:03:16,760 --> 01:03:17,720
Thank you, coach.

1282
01:03:17,720 --> 01:03:18,240
Thanks.

1283
01:03:23,480 --> 01:03:24,200
No, I just…

1284
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:26,160
Never seen your face this white.

1285
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,080
Are my friends over there?

1286
01:03:29,720 --> 01:03:30,320
Yeah.

1287
01:03:30,320 --> 01:03:32,800
Are my friends over there?

1288
01:03:32,800 --> 01:03:33,520
Yes.

1289
01:03:44,280 --> 01:03:44,920
Felt crazy good, huh?

1290
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:46,560
Was it awesome?

1291
01:03:46,560 --> 01:03:47,160
Awesome.

1292
01:03:53,600 --> 01:03:54,120
Felt crazy good, huh?

1293
01:03:54,120 --> 01:03:54,640
It was insanely good.

1294
01:03:55,160 --> 01:03:56,040
When we went through the clouds,

1295
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:57,000
my face almost froze solid.

1296
01:03:57,000 --> 01:03:58,360
I covered my face with my hands.

1297
01:03:58,360 --> 01:03:59,080
Yeah?

1298
01:03:59,080 --> 01:03:59,760
Lots of moisture.

1299
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:00,240
Yeah.

1300
01:04:00,560 --> 01:04:01,520
You can see the sunset up there.

1301
01:04:01,520 --> 01:04:02,160
Bing Ge.

1302
01:04:02,160 --> 01:04:02,560
Really?

1303
01:04:02,560 --> 01:04:03,080
Yeah.

1304
01:04:03,080 --> 01:04:04,080
Above the clouds there’s a sunset.

1305
01:04:04,480 --> 01:04:05,200
It’s really beautiful.

1306
01:04:05,200 --> 01:04:05,840
I’m telling you,

1307
01:04:05,840 --> 01:04:07,800
the sunset up there is stunning.

1308
01:04:07,800 --> 01:04:08,960
Hurry and take your gear off.

1309
01:04:08,960 --> 01:04:09,440
Hurry.

1310
01:04:09,440 --> 01:04:11,160
Come on, let’s go again.

1311
01:04:11,160 --> 01:04:11,840
Let’s go again.

1312
01:04:12,920 --> 01:04:14,720
I’ll even give you my flight jacket.

1313
01:04:15,320 --> 01:04:16,000
My lucky jacket.

1314
01:04:17,120 --> 01:04:17,640
Pretty good, right?

1315
01:04:17,640 --> 01:04:18,080
So good.

1316
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:19,760
Fits really well.

1317
01:04:19,760 --> 01:04:21,120
Totally worth it, bro.

1318
01:04:21,120 --> 01:04:21,880
Worth it, right?

1319
01:04:22,640 --> 01:04:23,960
The plane’s back.

1320
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:26,000
Why’s the plane flying like that?

1321
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:29,040
Now it’s showing off.

1322
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:35,280
It was just an exhibition jump.

1323
01:04:35,280 --> 01:04:35,840
A show jump.

1324
01:04:35,840 --> 01:04:37,080
We’re just putting on a show.

1325
01:04:37,080 --> 01:04:38,760
He didn’t get to enjoy it up there.

1326
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:40,200
So he’s flying for fun now.

1327
01:04:41,120 --> 01:04:41,360
Thanks.

1328
01:04:42,680 --> 01:04:45,280
Thank you.

1329
01:04:45,280 --> 01:04:47,040
The more I hear, the more I regret it.

1330
01:04:47,040 --> 01:04:49,240
Nothing to regret. A bet’s a bet.

1331
01:04:49,240 --> 01:04:49,960
A bet’s a bet.

1332
01:04:49,960 --> 01:04:51,160
I was checking my heart rate.

1333
01:04:52,200 --> 01:04:52,760
Over one hundred twenty.

1334
01:04:53,600 --> 01:04:54,920
That’s just normal,

1335
01:04:54,920 --> 01:04:56,240
like when you’re walking.

1336
01:04:56,240 --> 01:04:57,560
Up there it was just me

1337
01:04:57,560 --> 01:04:58,440
chatting with Bing Ge.

1338
01:04:58,440 --> 01:04:59,840
Sir Huang didn’t say a word.

1339
01:05:00,160 --> 01:05:01,360
Watch the replay later.

1340
01:05:01,360 --> 01:05:02,360
He never said a word.

1341
01:05:02,360 --> 01:05:03,320
Only before we jumped

1342
01:05:03,320 --> 01:05:05,400
I said, “Bing Ge, Sir Huang,

1343
01:05:06,480 --> 01:05:07,840
three, two, one, let’s go!”

1344
01:05:07,840 --> 01:05:09,120
Just that. Then nothing.

1345
01:05:11,080 --> 01:05:12,240
Impressive.

1346
01:05:12,840 --> 01:05:14,680
But it’s really great, not like—

1347
01:05:15,240 --> 01:05:16,520
I think this, compared to bungee,

1348
01:05:16,520 --> 01:05:17,520
is way more fun.

1349
01:05:17,920 --> 01:05:19,560
With bungee you have to get

1350
01:05:19,560 --> 01:05:20,240
yourself scared first,

1351
01:05:21,600 --> 01:05:22,640
then the weightlessness,

1352
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:23,280
then coming back up,

1353
01:05:24,120 --> 01:05:24,600
then weightless again.

1354
01:05:40,600 --> 01:05:41,120
I was also there going,

1355
01:05:42,040 --> 01:05:42,840
“Ahhh” for a while.

1356
01:05:42,840 --> 01:05:44,760
My teeth were freezing.

1357
01:05:44,760 --> 01:05:46,000
So I clenched them shut.

1358
01:05:46,000 --> 01:05:47,040
But without long johns, no way.

1359
01:05:47,040 --> 01:05:48,160
It’s really chilly up there.

1360
01:05:48,160 --> 01:05:49,080
Your hair right now is

1361
01:05:49,080 --> 01:05:49,960
“post‑skydive” hairstyle.

1362
01:05:49,960 --> 01:05:50,840
Don’t wear a hat.

1363
01:05:51,360 --> 01:05:52,680
That’s the hair of your bravery.

1364
01:05:52,680 --> 01:05:53,440
Why cover it up?

1365
01:05:53,440 --> 01:05:54,320
You make a good point.

1366
01:05:57,520 --> 01:05:59,160
Have you ever been in a cloud?

1367
01:06:02,240 --> 01:06:03,240
It’s so cold in there.

1368
01:06:04,960 --> 01:06:06,120
Feels full of tiny ice chips.

1369
01:06:06,640 --> 01:06:07,200
They whip against your face.

1370
01:06:07,200 --> 01:06:07,520
And then—

1371
01:06:07,520 --> 01:06:09,080
A Northeasterner hasn’t felt that?

1372
01:06:09,080 --> 01:06:10,280
When I bike a bit faster,

1373
01:06:10,280 --> 01:06:11,120
I already feel that.

1374
01:06:12,240 --> 01:06:13,480
This is Bing Ge’s first skydive.

1375
01:06:13,480 --> 01:06:14,080
First time.

1376
01:06:14,080 --> 01:06:14,600
How did it feel?

1377
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:16,880
Just pure fun.

1378
01:06:21,120 --> 01:06:22,200
Worth all this fuss after?

1379
01:06:22,200 --> 01:06:23,520
All this promotion for it?

1380
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:30,400
If I choose again, I pick this.

1381
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:31,000
I won’t pick bungee jumping.

1382
01:06:31,600 --> 01:06:33,400
Bungee is about challenging yourself.

1383
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:34,680
When you jump off,

1384
01:06:34,680 --> 01:06:35,800
you feel you’ve broken your limits.

1385
01:06:36,240 --> 01:06:37,920
This one really opened my eyes.

1386
01:06:38,400 --> 01:06:39,880
And while I was flying up there,

1387
01:06:39,880 --> 01:06:42,320
I wanted to do the Superman pose,

1388
01:06:42,800 --> 01:06:43,760
but I felt that would

1389
01:06:43,760 --> 01:06:45,200
probably throw off our balance.

1390
01:06:45,200 --> 01:06:46,080
We started spinning in circles.

1391
01:06:55,440 --> 01:06:56,040
So satisfying.

1392
01:06:56,720 --> 01:06:58,240
And when I was up there,

1393
01:06:58,240 --> 01:06:59,320
I was not nervous at all.

1394
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:00,080
Not nervous at all.

1395
01:07:00,080 --> 01:07:01,440
But when I came down I was pale.

1396
01:07:03,440 --> 01:07:04,400
It’s chilly up there.

1397
01:07:04,400 --> 01:07:05,200
It’s cold in the sky.

1398
01:07:05,200 --> 01:07:05,640
I was freezing.

1399
01:07:05,640 --> 01:07:06,040
So cold.

1400
01:07:06,040 --> 01:07:06,680
I really was freezing.

1401
01:07:06,680 --> 01:07:06,920
Yeah.

1402
01:07:07,320 --> 01:07:09,200
Our video is already out.

1403
01:07:09,200 --> 01:07:09,480
No, wait.

1404
01:07:09,480 --> 01:07:10,280
What video?

1405
01:07:10,280 --> 01:07:12,320
The video of your jump just now.

1406
01:07:13,400 --> 01:07:15,280
Did you manage your face well?

1407
01:07:16,800 --> 01:07:17,760
Then we’ve got it.

1408
01:07:17,760 --> 01:07:18,240
We’ve got it.

1409
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:20,560
Wang Anyu, want to step aside?

1410
01:07:21,960 --> 01:07:23,760
I kind of want to leave first.

1411
01:07:23,760 --> 01:07:24,320
But then I thought,

1412
01:07:24,320 --> 01:07:24,960
didn’t I just now also

1413
01:07:24,960 --> 01:07:26,080
brag a bit about it?

1414
01:07:28,200 --> 01:07:29,440
Down there with the guys,

1415
01:07:29,440 --> 01:07:31,480
I was boasting like crazy.

1416
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:32,600
Said I wasn’t scared at all.

1417
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:34,440
Then they played the video.

1418
01:07:38,080 --> 01:07:39,560
Let’s watch Sir Huang’s first.

1419
01:07:39,560 --> 01:07:40,920
No, watch Anyu’s first.

1420
01:07:41,600 --> 01:07:42,320
Sure, either way, go in order.

1421
01:07:42,320 --> 01:07:43,160
An Yu, Bing Ge, then me—

1422
01:07:43,160 --> 01:07:44,200
that’s how the three of us jumped.

1423
01:07:44,200 --> 01:07:45,400
We can follow that order.

1424
01:07:45,400 --> 01:07:46,040
Me.

1425
01:07:46,040 --> 01:07:46,720
I’ll embarrass myself first.

1426
01:07:47,320 --> 01:07:49,240
Show them the moment the door opens.

1427
01:07:49,240 --> 01:07:49,560
When the door opens,

1428
01:07:49,560 --> 01:07:50,720
it’s super nerve‑racking.

1429
01:07:50,720 --> 01:07:52,000
Look at An Yu’s reaction.

1430
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:54,000
Such a change from door closed to open.

1431
01:07:59,000 --> 01:08:01,240
An Yu studied English so long,

1432
01:08:01,240 --> 01:08:02,280
and in the end he only shouted,

1433
01:08:07,400 --> 01:08:08,120
Watch An Yu.

1434
01:08:08,560 --> 01:08:09,960
Everyone,

1435
01:08:12,160 --> 01:08:12,680
An Yu—

1436
01:08:12,680 --> 01:08:13,480
“You only live once!”

1437
01:08:15,040 --> 01:08:16,200
“You only live once!”

1438
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:17,000
He wouldn’t let me shout it.

1439
01:08:17,000 --> 01:08:18,200
“You only live once,” see that?

1440
01:08:18,600 --> 01:08:19,080
He didn’t even finish.

1441
01:08:19,080 --> 01:08:20,800
“An Yu, you only live once!”

1442
01:08:20,800 --> 01:08:21,920
The coach said, “What are you doing?”

1443
01:08:23,680 --> 01:08:24,920
“Get your hands back here!”

1444
01:08:32,439 --> 01:08:33,399
That felt amazing.

1445
01:08:34,279 --> 01:08:35,600
This part looks the best.

1446
01:08:36,880 --> 01:08:37,840
A once‑in‑a‑lifetime shot.

1447
01:08:41,040 --> 01:08:42,160
Why don’t we see Bing Ge’s face?

1448
01:08:46,720 --> 01:08:47,840
Bing Ge is just enjoying it.

1449
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:51,640
Bing Ge went up for a free

1450
01:08:51,640 --> 01:08:52,240
what do you call it—

1451
01:08:52,680 --> 01:08:53,399
a lift…

1452
01:08:53,399 --> 01:08:54,200
Pilates.

1453
01:08:54,200 --> 01:08:54,800
Not Pilates.

1454
01:08:54,800 --> 01:08:55,240
What’s it called then?

1455
01:08:55,240 --> 01:08:56,040
Feels like his skin

1456
01:08:56,040 --> 01:08:57,479
is getting yanked loose.

1457
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:00,600
Look how calm I am.

1458
01:09:00,600 --> 01:09:00,880
Sir Huang.

1459
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:02,120
Sir Huang.

1460
01:09:03,479 --> 01:09:04,520
Why does it look like

1461
01:09:04,520 --> 01:09:06,200
you struggled going down?

1462
01:09:07,000 --> 01:09:07,680
Was I struggling?

1463
01:09:12,080 --> 01:09:13,120
You’re unbelievable.

1464
01:09:15,399 --> 01:09:16,439
What is this from you?

1465
01:09:21,760 --> 01:09:23,000
You got down and pretended.

1466
01:09:23,000 --> 01:09:24,279
Turns out you’re the biggest poser.

1467
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:26,960
Was it really like that?

1468
01:09:27,800 --> 01:09:29,760
I remember during training

1469
01:09:29,760 --> 01:09:30,600
they told me to keep my head up.

1470
01:09:30,600 --> 01:09:31,240
Head up?

1471
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:42,800
Was I that pathetic coming down?

1472
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:45,120
In my mind I was like this—

1473
01:09:46,000 --> 01:09:46,640
Let’s go.

1474
01:09:46,640 --> 01:09:47,200
But actually…

1475
01:09:49,720 --> 01:09:50,720
I’ve never seen you anywhere

1476
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,080
this shy and bashful.

1477
01:09:55,680 --> 01:09:56,840
You three were awesome.

1478
01:10:01,560 --> 01:10:02,760
Next season, it’s Jingyu’s turn.

1479
01:10:02,760 --> 01:10:03,720
He should learn that…

1480
01:10:03,720 --> 01:10:04,880
a pilot’s license.

1481
01:10:04,880 --> 01:10:06,000
I’ll fly the plane and take you up.

1482
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:07,320
Will we even make it back, bro?

1483
01:11:05,080 --> 01:11:06,440
We'll be experiencing

1484
01:11:06,440 --> 01:11:08,080
European manor life here.

1485
01:11:08,080 --> 01:11:09,520
You can all give your gifts now.

1486
01:11:09,520 --> 01:11:10,800
Mine is for Teng Ge.

1487
01:11:10,800 --> 01:11:11,680
I think this

1488
01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:12,320
height

1489
01:11:12,320 --> 01:11:14,680
really suits Teng Ge's long legs.

1490
01:11:14,680 --> 01:11:16,280
Mine might be a bit shorter though.

1491
01:11:16,280 --> 01:11:17,600
Yeah, because your upper body’s long.

1492
01:11:17,600 --> 01:11:18,400
Darn it.

1493
01:11:18,400 --> 01:11:19,400
And your arms are short.

1494
01:11:20,360 --> 01:11:21,560
I got one for you too.

1495
01:11:21,560 --> 01:11:22,240
Wrapped it together.

1496
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:23,160
It's not just air, right?

1497
01:11:29,040 --> 01:11:30,840
They upgraded this game.

1498
01:11:30,840 --> 01:11:31,920
All because last time you said

1499
01:11:31,920 --> 01:11:33,240
you’d cracked the code.

1500
01:11:33,240 --> 01:11:34,480
I even forgot that.

1501
01:11:34,760 --> 01:11:36,360
You take what he says too seriously.

1502
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:39,640
Why is everyone so quiet?

1503
01:11:39,640 --> 01:11:40,280
Not saying a single word.

1504
01:11:40,280 --> 01:11:41,520
All here pretending to be smart.

1505
01:11:41,520 --> 01:11:43,080
Just brains whirring everywhere.

1506
01:11:44,600 --> 01:11:46,080
Three, two, one, everyone close eyes.

1507
01:11:46,080 --> 01:11:47,040
Bro, let's team up, bro.

1508
01:11:47,040 --> 01:11:48,440
You won't “kill” me, right?

1509
01:11:48,960 --> 01:11:49,680
I opened my eyes.

1510
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:50,840
I'm heading this way now.

1511
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:52,320
Xiao Hu.

1512
01:11:52,320 --> 01:11:52,920
Xiao Hu is “dead.”

1513
01:11:52,920 --> 01:11:53,560
Call the cops.

1514
01:11:53,560 --> 01:11:55,040
My first instinct is to vote Chengcheng.

1515
01:11:55,040 --> 01:11:56,320
I don't think Chengcheng

1516
01:11:56,320 --> 01:11:57,480
is that sophisticated.

1517
01:11:57,480 --> 01:11:58,040
After all, he's

1518
01:11:58,040 --> 01:11:59,840
a kid born in 2000.

1519
01:12:00,640 --> 01:12:02,560
Let's join up and take him out.

1520
01:12:02,560 --> 01:12:03,320
If this works,

1521
01:12:03,320 --> 01:12:04,240
we’re the smart ones.

1522
01:12:04,240 --> 01:12:05,440
If it doesn’t,

1523
01:12:05,440 --> 01:12:06,400
then I’m just dumb.

1524
01:12:06,400 --> 01:12:06,920
You two with these—

1525
01:12:06,920 --> 01:12:07,840
what is this, nunchucks?

1526
01:12:09,120 --> 01:12:10,280
Come, a duel for dignity.

1527
01:12:10,520 --> 01:12:11,040
Please vote.

1528
01:12:13,840 --> 01:12:15,200
Next, the challenge levels up.

1529
01:12:16,920 --> 01:12:19,080
With Jingyu, I feel our team can win.

1530
01:12:19,080 --> 01:12:21,160
I don’t really get this word now.

1531
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:22,200
Come on, little bro.

1532
01:12:22,200 --> 01:12:26,800
Night of Ulan Bator.

1533
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:28,520
Does this still involve the old lady?

1534
01:12:29,880 --> 01:12:30,640
Ulan—

1535
01:12:31,840 --> 01:12:33,280
Was that part of the act just now?

1536
01:12:34,280 --> 01:12:37,640
You can't even hear the wind.

1537
01:12:37,640 --> 01:12:39,600
Can't hear it.

1538
01:12:44,360 --> 01:12:47,080
From behind I saw his cheeks were—

1539
01:12:48,640 --> 01:12:49,440
Okay, that’s enough.

1540
01:12:50,160 --> 01:12:51,120
Sir Huang got them all wrong.

1541
01:12:51,120 --> 01:12:52,560
Sir Huang can’t even change them now.

1542
01:12:52,560 --> 01:12:54,200
Give us a super hard one.

1543
01:12:54,200 --> 01:12:54,640
This one?

1544
01:12:54,640 --> 01:12:55,400
Don't tell me it's this.

1545
01:12:55,400 --> 01:12:55,720
Yeah.

1546
01:12:59,160 --> 01:13:00,840
For this, your facial muscles

1547
01:13:00,840 --> 01:13:02,160
must be controlled so well,

1548
01:13:02,160 --> 01:13:03,760
to pull off that twisted smile.

1549
01:13:03,760 --> 01:13:06,280
You can’t do it on purpose.

1550
01:13:06,280 --> 01:13:07,200
And still sing?

1551
01:13:07,640 --> 01:13:08,680
That twisted, crossed-up smile.

1552
01:13:08,680 --> 01:13:09,960
Who’ll show it for me?

1553
01:13:09,960 --> 01:13:11,160
I’ll bow three times to you.

1554
01:13:12,360 --> 01:13:14,920
Wish you brilliance.

1555
01:13:15,800 --> 01:13:17,360
That’s terrifying.

1556
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:19,040
I wish you wealth.

1557
01:13:19,040 --> 01:13:20,480
I wish you brilliance.

1558
01:13:20,480 --> 01:13:22,480
Why is no one playing “Spy”?

1559
01:13:22,480 --> 01:13:23,680
Where did the Spy go?
